Then $OM = r + 30 - 2r = 30 - r$, so $NOM$ is a $30^\circ$-$60^\circ$-$90^\circ$ triangle.  Therefore, $ON = (30 - r) \sqrt{3}$.  The desired area is the area of $\mathcal{C}$ minus the area of the six small circles, or
\[K = \pi \cdot 30^2 - 6 \cdot \pi r^2.\]The area of $\triangle MON$ is
\[\frac{1}{2} \cdot OM \cdot ON = \frac{1}{2} (30 - r)(30 - r) \sqrt{3}.\]Therefore, the area inside $\mathcal{C}$ and outside the six circles is
\[K = \pi \cdot 30^2 - 6 \cdot \pi r^2 = 900 \pi - 3 \pi (30 - r)^2.\]Thus,
\[\lfloor K \rfloor = 900 \pi - 3 \pi (30 - r)^2 < 900 \pi,\]so $\lfloor K \rfloor = \boxed{2826}$.
